 come together to share why they joined the theatre and how it transformed their lives. Teatro Chicana tells the story of this troupe through chapters featuring the history and present-day story of each of the main actors and writers, as well as excerpts from the group's materials and seven of their original short scripts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAmerican dramaxMexican American authors. 0aAmerican dramaxWomen authors. 0aAmerican dramay20th century. 0aFeminist theaterzCaliforniazSan DiegoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexican American theaterzCaliforniazSan DiegoxHistoryy20th century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBroyles-Gonzalez, Yolanda.1 aBroyles-González, Yolanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcia, Laura E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGutierrez, Sandra M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNuñez, Felicitas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/71743540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292794559423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292794559/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK